For each of the {= public_actor_group =} public actor groups listed below, identify {= public_event =}+ dated public events or filed public artifacts connected to California hydrogen power, utility operations, public funding or procurement, public-program implementation, RPS or policy treatment, hub or cluster development, or public-authority procurement as of {= target_as_of_date =}; for each event, cover each `evidence_role` listed below with a role-specific public source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL) that substantiates the named public actor, event title, event date, and public-process context.

The public actor groups are:
- `state_energy_program`: California state energy-program agencies, boards, offices, dockets, grants, solicitations, workshops, awards, and program implementation actions.
- `state_regulatory_or_legislative`: California state regulatory, legislative, gubernatorial, docket, bill, proceeding, RPS, tariff, rulemaking, or comparable public-policy actions.
- `utility_or_public_power`: investor-owned utilities, public-power agencies, joint power agencies, municipal utilities, power authorities, utility filings, utility solicitations, grid or power-plant modernization actions, and public-power procurement or planning events.
- `federal_hub_or_arches`: federal hydrogen-hub, ARCHES, DOE, NEPA, Federal Register, award, milestone, scoping, environmental-review, or directly related public-project actions for the California Hydrogen Hub.
- `local_public_authority_or_procurement`: city, county, port, transit, air district, regional authority, local public-agency, or public-authority procurement, award, board, agenda, funding, infrastructure, or deployment actions.

The event/action/document date controls the cutoff. Events dated on or before {= target_as_of_date =} count even when page publication metadata is later; pages whose only date evidence is after {= target_as_of_date =} are outside scope. `public_event` should be a real dated public event, official action, solicitation, award, filed public document, hearing/workshop, bill action, utility filing, public-authority procurement, or federal hub/NEPA milestone. Broad hydrogen explainers, generic refueling directories, market reports, investment analysis, lead lists, directory pages, and procurement recommendations are outside this public-event scope. Docket comments and filed stakeholder materials count only as filed public artifacts, not as agency adoption, project approval, or official policy unless the page itself states that separate public action.

